{"author":{"id":"b815c53718a0d7121846b81e1c820fdbcf27ef19124fbf0a3f1f9fcc65f67df7"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1519226209,"nonce":"qT+JvQSYqnCbLiz8qNzvDCBWyTI=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyOTkwMDk1NzY=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1733","origin":"github"},"title":"BWA does not properly report errors","message":"if e.g. ```bwa sampe``` command fails with error ```[fread] Unexpected end of file``` the error code is not able to be used, because its output is being piped into ```samtools sort```. Since a header is being written by ```bwa sampe```, the  ```samtools sort``` command completes successfully and the output dataset is an OK green header-only bam file. \n\nThis output should be in the error state.\n\nThis is a generalizable problem with using pipes (```|```) within tools, as return codes are not propagated down the line, but can be found by examining e.g. ```$PIPESTATUS```.\n\n\nAn easy workaround is to add a special catch for ```[fread] Unexpected end of file``` to the growing lists of error ```\u003cregex match\u003e``` strings in the tool, but this is not advisable nor sustainable, as it becomes a 'game' of trying to find all of the errors, instead of properly relying on the command's exit codes. \n\n\nexample command:\n```\nln -s '/export/galaxy-central/database/files/024/dataset_24239.dat' 'localref.fa' \u0026\u0026 bwa index 'localref.fa' \u0026\u0026                            bwa aln -t \"${GALAXY_SLOTS:-1}\"   'localref.fa' '/export/galaxy-central/database/files/024/dataset_24063.dat' \u003e first.sai \u0026\u0026  bwa aln -t \"${GALAXY_SLOTS:-1}\"   'localref.fa' '/export/galaxy-central/database/files/024/dataset_24064.dat' \u003e second.sai \u0026\u0026  bwa sampe    -r '@RG\\tID:str8'  'localref.fa' first.sai second.sai '/export/galaxy-central/database/files/024/dataset_24063.dat' '/export/galaxy-central/database/files/024/dataset_24064.dat'    | samtools sort -@${GALAXY_SLOTS:-2} -O bam -o '/export/galaxy-central/database/files/024/dataset_24253.dat'\n```\n\nexample tool stderr:\n```\n[bwa_index] Pack FASTA... 0.06 sec\n[bwa_index] Construct BWT for the packed sequence...\n[bwa_index] 4.03 seconds elapse.\n[bwa_index] Update BWT... 0.07 sec\n[bwa_index] Pack forward-only FASTA... 0.05 sec\n[bwa_index] Construct SA from BWT and Occ... 1.77 sec\n[main] Version: 0.7.17-r1188\n[main] CMD: bwa index localref.fa\n[main] Real time: 9.673 sec; CPU: 5.970 sec\n[bwa_aln] 17bp reads: max_diff = 2\n[bwa_aln] 38bp reads: max_diff = 3\n[bwa_aln] 64bp reads: max_diff = 4\n[bwa_aln] 93bp reads: max_diff = 5\n[bwa_aln] 124bp reads: max_diff = 6\n[bwa_aln] 157bp reads: max_diff = 7\n[bwa_aln] 190bp reads: max_diff = 8\n[bwa_aln] 225bp reads: max_diff = 9\n[bwa_aln_core] calculate SA coordinate... 0.99 sec\n[bwa_aln_core] write to the disk... 0.00 sec\n[bwa_aln_core] 39106 sequences have been processed.\n[main] Version: 0.7.17-r1188\n[main] CMD: bwa aln -t 1 localref.fa /export/galaxy-central/database/files/024/dataset_24063.dat\n[main] Real time: 2.273 sec; CPU: 1.067 sec\n[bwa_aln] 17bp reads: max_diff = 2\n[bwa_aln] 38bp reads: max_diff = 3\n[bwa_aln] 64bp reads: max_diff = 4\n[bwa_aln] 93bp reads: max_diff = 5\n[bwa_aln] 124bp reads: max_diff = 6\n[bwa_aln] 157bp reads: max_diff = 7\n[bwa_aln] 190bp reads: max_diff = 8\n[bwa_aln] 225bp reads: max_diff = 9\n[bwa_aln_core] calculate SA coordinate... 0.94 sec\n[bwa_aln_core] write to the disk... 0.00 sec\n[bwa_aln_core] 39113 sequences have been processed.\n[main] Version: 0.7.17-r1188\n[main] CMD: bwa aln -t 1 localref.fa /export/galaxy-central/database/files/024/dataset_24064.dat\n[main] Real time: 2.052 sec; CPU: 1.010 sec\n[bwa_sai2sam_pe_core] convert to sequence coordinate... \n[fread] Unexpected end of file\n```","files":null}]}